phrases: I will hear you guys out.
Why are you on this side?!
I would appreciate if you would forget that.
There is something I am counting on you to do.
May I talk to you for a bit?
Once I am past here, the rest is easy.
I just need to talk to the rest of them, one at a time.
That could very well help me figure out who the fake Itsuki is.
I doubt they have anything serious on their minds, anyway.
Come on, Futaro-kun, learn to knock first.
I wanted to try this on you again anyway.
Do you remember the quintuplets game?
Why do not you try guessing who is who?
I definitely feel happy when I am having good food.
Uesugi-kun, you must not ask such questions of a girl!
Damn it, I cannot tell them apart at all.
If you do not have any more questions...
Why are you all impersonating Itsuki?
It is a long story, but...
The five of us quintuplets have always looked identical,
and everyone could see that we were tight-knit.
Grandpa was happy to see it, too.
But one day, I tried dressing up differently from everyone else.
The same-bunny ear ribbon that I wear...
I-I have no idea what you are talking about!
Given how she is the worst liar, I figured she would be easy to find, but not that easy.
L-Let Itsuki take over from here.
Grandpa became worried when he saw that the five of us were not the same anymore.
He thought we might have had a falling out.
And since then, we have decided to look the same when we are around him.
And after some discussion, we decided we would be Itsuki.
So once spring break started and we decided we would be coming here,
I have been worried that I might not be able to pull off the look.
Is that what is been bugging you this whole time?
Everyone seemed to be having fun, so I did not want to bring it up.
You do all that for that scary old man?
He is a very kind man.
It might be a stupid worry to me, but it is serious for them.
Well, can you tell us apart, now that you have talked to us?
I had it a second ago!
We are all still the same, best buddies.
I was afraid it was their dad, but this is fine.
If Fake Itsuki is here, one of them might have a bruise from last night.
What do you think you are doing?!
Want to go to the main hall?
Want to go take a morning bath?
May I have a word with you?
You are doing this on purpose.
I legit cannot figure it out.
You do not have to do that.
So why is it me this time?
Y'know, you get it a lot, do not you?
I cannot talk to the other girls about it.
I am in dire need of food!
Yup, that is how Itsuki would say it.
S-So we went to buy curtains,
but all of us had differing tastes.
How long do I need to be here for?
We all chose different curtains, and things got kind of ugly at one point.
I have not even had breakfast yet.
I am in dire need of some food!
You must have been surprised when you saw Dad with us.
I accidentally wrote our old address when I signed up for the giveaway with you.
Although we all got to be here together as a result.
I could never tell from how she looks.
Itsuki says there is something bothering Miku, too.
I think I have got a rough idea of what it is, and it happened last month.
Do not tell me, what is bothering Miku is...
Since when did I bother thinking about this kind of thing?
I feel a creepy stare on me.
Please stop being mean and tell me.
I want you to get it right, too, Futaro.
At least show me your legs, then.
I saw you trying to lay your hands on my granddaughter again.
I have not done anything today.
Miku, has he done anything to you?
That old man figured out she is Miku just by looking at her.
Miku, I will catch up later.
I wanted to ask for relationship advice.
The way I met him was the worst.
But I went on to realize that I love him.
I told him how I felt just the other day.
But I do not know if I did the right thing.
When someone confesses to you, do you think about them more?
If I am just speaking from experience...
Sorry, I do not think it worked out that way for me.
I have feelings for Futaro-kun, too.
So please, let me keep things the way they are for now.
Oh, so just telling him how I feel is not enough?
You said it was horrible the way you met him, right?
Are you sure you love him?
He appeared as a force of destruction against something that was dear to me.
But one night, I mistook him for my Prince Charming and fell in love.
And soon, I came to realize
that what I rejected was his role and not him as a person.
Once I realized that he was my prince, I could not control myself anymore.
And you fell in love, just like that?
Do not you think that is too self-centered?
I creep myself out too, honestly.
I do not intend to give up, though.
I mean, this is my love.
What is the point if it does not make me happy?
Wh-What if there is someone else who likes the same guy?
What if that person cares about him way more than you do?
I would feel bad, but I would walk over them to get with him, if I had to.
I think that is how I would feel.
She is a runaway train of love!
She will not even listen to me!
I am glad I talked to you.
I guess a confession is not enough.
What are you going to do?!
And if he still does not take the hint,
Th-That is not a good idea!
You should not kiss him out of nowhere!
He will be turned off if I am bad at it.
Have you done any kiss scenes yet?!
Wh-What do you think you are doing?
It is wrong because we are sisters!
I am going to sneak out at night to see him.
Dad's going to be a problem when I do.
So I need you to keep an eye on him for me, Ichika.
Nino's going to meet up with Futaro-kun.
And she might even kiss him.
She is not a coward like I am.
She does not care what anyone thinks.
She loves him with everything she has.
I do not even stand a chance.
I do not have the right.
I know, it is been a while.
Let us go to our secret place.
He would never expect us to be up here.
I am supposed to stop him for Nino.
I do not know what is going on, but...
It still gets chilly at night.
You should not have come out so lightly dressed.
You are always such a child.
You are trying to cheer me up, right?
I have to go after Dad.
Are you trying to be tough?
Sorry if I am just overthinking it.
What if they are with Futaro?
There is no reason to see him so late at night.
Just waiting here will not help.
Why do not we go to the baths?
I have been thinking about the old days since we got here.
Like how Grandpa used to be really scary.
Or how Mom scolded us all the time for our mischief.
You were the one who got in the most trouble.
Do not tell me you forgot.
Even among us identical twins, you were the big bully figure.
I lost count of the number of times you stole my snacks.
The stickers I would been collecting were on your backpack.
And I saw people who I tried to be friends with talking to you the next day.
I-I guess I have grown up since then.
I have stayed a kid this whole time.
How come you were able to grow up?
I saw Itsuki-chan in so much pain after Mom died.
I had to be the older sister.
I am glad you are my older sister.
I have been wanting to say this.
As a kid, you were the mean bully, always wanting to take things from other people.
But you were the leader of us sisters.
I have always thought of you as our big sis.
Wait, what was I trying to say?
I do not want you to hold back.
I want you to do what you want to do, I guess.
I wanted these times to go on forever.
I always wanted to be here in this comfort zone.
I did not want anyone else to take him.
You are taking it back after you lent it to me?!
Okay, let us go back inside.
So, did not you have to go see Dad?
That is what I was about to say!
I was about to say it!
Just give me a little longer!
Your grandpa's about to teach me!
He has no intention of figuring it out himself.
There is no way he can learn to tell us apart after just half a year.
Is not there a trick or something to telling them apart?
You can tell them apart if you have love.
So he is the one who started it!
Over a long time, you learn to identify their mannerisms, voice, subtle habits...
You said you wanted to tell my grandkids apart.
Why do you want to tell my grandkids apart?
What is it you want to accomplish by being able to tell them apart?
Do you have the commitment to face them in good faith?
Can I assume you are the Itsuki I talked to on the first night?
I never did figure out how to win the quintuplet game.
But I do not like being a loser.
I am going to figure you out myself, even if I get no one else.
That is my show of commitment to facing you sisters in good faith.
Itsuki has told you what is going on, correct?
First, Yotsuba's problem is with this trip itself.
Therefore, at the end of today, she no longer has to worry.
She is not as perfect an impersonator as you.
She forgot to remove her pedicure.
You were always the most cooperative.
Why are you trying to end your relationship with Uesugi-kun?
I have to apologize to you first.
I was in a panic because Grandpa was there.
No, that is an excuse, too.
I could not tell him as myself.
You have a crush on Uesugi-kun?!
Everyone is going to be shocked when they hear!
I am pretty sure everyone knows.
We are technically students and teacher.
He and I are teacher and student.
If this goes on, our relationship will never change.
Please meet Uesugi-kun one last time.
Therefore, you are not Nino, either.
Then what is it that is on Nino's mind?
That is one thing I should not say.
You are either Ichika or Miku.
If I think of her as Ichika, she looks like Ichika.
But that goes for Miku, too.
Could you call her for me?
Oh, that is what he is doing.
Ichika's the only one who calls her Itsuki- chan!
Sheesh, you made me waste so much time.
I figured it would be you, since I could not figure out what was bothering you.
I heard it is gotten busy.
Well, I have to get ready for the trip home.
Over a long time, you learn to identify their mannerisms, voice, subtle habits...
This is the only way I can tell them apart.
I might be imagining it, but for a second,
You seemed to have a hunch about what was bugging me.
If I was not Fake Itsuki, what would you have thought it was?
It is an embarrassing thought, now that I know I was wrong...
I will tell you, so do not laugh.
I thought you were mad because I did not give you anything in return after V-Day.
Why did you want me to quit, anyway?
My grandkids are all I have to live for,
now that I have lost Rena.
Tell my grandkids to stay true to themselves.
Over a long time, you learn to identify their mannerisms, voice, subtle habits...
If that is true, then the reason I knew it was Miku...
In any case, it is true that I could tell them apart.
